{{Quote|I am your experience, so experience me.|Mermeia|<ref name="Fever Dream">''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''</ref>}}
'''Pornography''' was a type of media often produced in the form of [[Hologram/Legends|holos]], with some [[holoporn]] being illegal. It was available through both [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojectors]] and [[Mind evaporator/Legends|mind evaporators]], showing the user the [[virtual reality]] [[Gender/Legends|woman]] [[Mermeia]]. Between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], pornography could be found in the [[Black market/Legends|black market]] on [[Planet/Legends|planets]] that were either affiliated with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] or close to its bases. Around [[1 ABY/Legends|1.5 ABY]], the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Attichitcuk/Legends|Attichitcuk]] had an erotic interaction with Mermeia after receiving a [[Brain/Legends|mind]] evaporator [[cassette]] from the [[Merchant/Legends|trader]] [[Saun Dann]] for the [[Life Day/Legends|Life Day]] holiday.

The [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]-owned [[Kailio Entertainments]] was a distributor for one of the largest holoporn industries in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] around [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]], during which [[Standard year/Legends|year]] the [[Lucin Syndicate]] also ran an illegal holoporn operation. By [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]], the Hutt [[Beldorion]] possessed a large library of Hutt holoporn and hired the [[holo faker]] [[Liegeus Vorn]] to retape it.

==Description==
{{Quote|I am in your mind, as you create me.|Mermeia|<ref name="Fever Dream" />}}
[[File:Mermeia.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Mermeia, as seen by Attichitcuk]]
Pornography was usually produced in the form of [[Hologram/Legends|holos]]. Such [[holoporn]] could be either legal or illegal.<ref name="GG11" /> Pornography<ref name="Comedy Hour 3">{{WebCite|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/magazine/2008/12/star_wars_special200812?currentPage=3|text=The Han Solo Comedy Hour! (page 3 of 3)|work=Vanity Fair|archivedate=20081225130516}}</ref> involving the [[virtual reality]]<ref name="Insider23" /> [[Gender/Legends|woman]] [[Mermeia]]<ref name="Insider106">{{InsiderCite|106|I Have a Bad Feeling About This!}}</ref>&mdash;bearing a form created by the [[Brain/Legends|mind]] of the being who perceived<ref name="Fever Dream" /> her<ref name="Insider106" />&mdash;could be accessed through [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojectors]],<ref name="SWG Thought">{{SWGTCG|set=Threat of the Conqueror|cardname=Thought as Action}}</ref> and also through [[Mind evaporator/Legends|mind evaporators]],<ref name="Fever Dream" /> also known as [[Proton/Legends|proton]] chairs,<ref name="Galaxies">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=item|Proton Chair}}</ref> upon entering specific [[cassette]]s,<ref name="Fever Dream" /> though this type of pornography did not necessarily have to involve Mermeia.<ref name="Galaxies" /> Such pornography could involve [[Music/Legends|singing]] and dancing.<ref name="Fever Dream" />

{{Talesstart}}
Pornography was also sometimes referred to as smut.<ref name="SB">{{Tales|14|Smuggler's Blues}}</ref>
{{Talesend}}

==History==
===Age of the Empire===
{{Talesstart}}
{{Quote|I've gotta shipment of holographic ''Hutt-smut'' that absolutely, positively ''must'' be delivered overnight to the ''Kurluvion'' system. They just ''love'' Hutt-smut there, can't get enough.|A Snivvian|<ref name="SB" />}}
In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="SBDate">"[[Smuggler's Blues]]" takes place concurrently with the portion of {{Film|IV}} that ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' places in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]].</ref> a [[Unidentified Snivvian (Chalmun's Cantina)|Snivvian]] approached the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] in [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Cantina]]<ref name="SB" /> in the [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].<ref name="CL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2005)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'', 2005 edition]]</ref> The [[Snivvian/Legends|Snivvian]] told Solo that they had a shipment of holographic [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] pornography that they wanted delivered to the [[Kurluvion system/Legends|Kurluvion system]], claiming that the [[Star system/Legends|system's]] population loved Hutt holoporn. Solo refused the job offer, telling the Snivvian that<ref name="SB" /> he<ref name="CL" /> had integrity and considered being [[Carbon-freezing/Legends|frozen]] in [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]] preferable to smuggling Hutt pornography.<ref name="SB" />
{{Talesend}}

Between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="GG6Date">''[[Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters]]'' and its [[Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters (Second Edition)|second edition]] are both set between the events of {{Film|IV}} and {{Film|VI}}, which corresponds to between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] per ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> it was possible to find pornographic holos on the [[Black market/Legends|black market]] of planets affiliated with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|against]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]<ref name="GG6">''[[Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters]]''</ref> as well as planets located near the Rebellion's bases.<ref name="GG6 2nd" /> Between 0 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]] and approximately [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="TCGDate">The ''[[Threat of the Conqueror]]'' expansion of [[Star Wars Galaxies Trading Card Game|''Star Wars Galaxies'' Trading Card Game]] takes place at some point during [[Star Wars Galaxies|''Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided'']]{{'s}} events, which are set between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and approximately [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]] per the reasoning [[Template:SWG timeline|here]].</ref> a [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] watched a hologram of Mermeia dancing.<ref name="SWG Thought" />

===Life Day===
{{Quote|I am here. My voice is for you alone.|Mermeia|<ref name="Fever Dream" />}}
[[File:Evaporator.jpg|thumb|left|240px|Saun Dann set up the mind evaporator for Attichitcuk.]]
Around 1.5 ABY,<ref name="HolidayDate">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=870#15778940|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2006-10-12|time=6:13 PM}}</ref> the [[Merchant/Legends|trader]] [[Saun Dann]] gifted the elderly [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Attichitcuk/Legends|Attichitcuk]] a cassette for the Wookiee holiday [[Life Day/Legends|Life Day]]. Dann inserted the cassette into a mind evaporator in Attichitcuk's [[Chewbacca's home|home]]<ref name="Fever Dream" /> in the [[City/Legends|city]] [[Rwookrrorro/Legends|Rwookrrorro]] on the planet [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]].<ref name="Tyrant's Test">''[[Tyrant's Test]]''</ref> Wishing the Wookiee a happy Life Day, the [[Human/Legends|Human]] turned the mind evaporator on and left Attichitcuk alone. Through the mind evaporator, Attichitcuk saw Mermeia, whose form was created by<ref name="Fever Dream" /> his<ref name="Attichitcuk DB">{{DB|character|itchy|Attichitcuk}}</ref> mind. During the following<ref name="Fever Dream" /> erotic<ref name="Insider23" /> experience, Mermeia flirted with Attichitcuk and sang to him a [[This Minute Now|song]] about her longing to stay with the Wookiee before vanishing into a kaleidoscopic background.<ref name="Fever Dream" />

{{Gamemechanics|Star Wars Galaxies}}
Elsewhere during that holiday,<ref name="SWG Life Day date">In a [https://web.archive.org/web/20061115064750/https://forums.starwars.com/thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=870#15778940 post] on the [[StarWars.com Message Boards]] forum, [[Holocron continuity database|Holocron]] keeper [[Leland Chee]] has stated that [[Life Day/Legends|Life Day]] is celebrated once every three [[Standard year/Legends|years]]; that the one depicted in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'' takes place around [[1 ABY/Legends|1.5 ABY]]; and that the several Life Days portrayed in the ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'' [[Star Wars video games|video game]] each occurred around [[Wikipedia:Christmas|Christmas]] in real-world time. Given that the timeline of ''Galaxies'' only spans from [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] to approximately 1 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]] per the reasoning [[Template:SWG timeline|here]] and therefore can not fit multiple Life Days, this article treats all of the holidays within the game to be the same Life Day that occurred around 1.5 ABY as depicted in ''The Star Wars Holiday Special''.</ref> a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] bought a proton chair during the Life Day and brought it home, after which they used it to listen to a voice speak to them.<ref name="Galaxies">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=item|Proton Chair}}</ref>
{{Endgame}}

===Syndicates and Hutts===
{{Quote|Beldorion has drafted me into editing and retaping his formidable library of Huttese pornography.|Liegeus Vorn|<ref name="PoT">''[[Planet of Twilight]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Kailio_Entertainments.svg|thumb|right|220px|Kailio Entertainments (logo pictured) was a holoporn distributor.]]
Around [[10 ABY/Legends|10 ABY]],<ref name="GG11Date">''[[Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations]]'' is set around six [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after {{Film|VI}}, the events of which ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> the Hutt-owned [[Kailio Entertainments]] was a distributor for one of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] biggest holoporn industries. Around the same time, the [[Lucin Syndicate]] was based on the world [[Majilop]], from which they operated a major [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] center for production and distribution of illegal holoporn.<ref name="GG11" /> By [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]],<ref name="PoTDate">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''[[Planet of Twilight]]'' to [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]].</ref> the Hutt ruler [[Beldorion]] of the planet [[Nam Chorios/Legends|Nam Chorios]] owned a large library of holographic Huttese pornography and commissioned the Human [[holo faker]] [[Liegeus Vorn]] to edit and retape the collection.<ref name="PoT" /> That [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="PoTDate" /> Vorn shared that fact with the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] representative [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and mentioned that not even his former job of [[Author/Legends|ghost-writing]] love [[Gamorrean poetry|poems]] for [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorreans]] had made him as frightened.<ref name="PoT" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:StarWarsHS.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Pornography first appeared in ''The Star Wars Holiday Special''.]]
Pornography first appeared in the film ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'',<ref name="Fever Dream" /> released in [[1978]].<ref name="Boba Fett: Mystery Man">{{GalaxyCite|1|Boba Fett: Mystery Man in Not-So-Shining Armor}}</ref> According to<ref name="Comedy Hour 3" /> producer<ref name="SW">{{SWArchive|url=movies/saga/20081117.html|text=Holiday Special: Script and Directors}}</ref> [[Mitzie Welch]], Mermeia's scene in ''The Star Wars Holiday Special'' was intended to be [[Wikipedia:Softcore pornography|softcore pornography]] that would pass through censorship.<ref name="Comedy Hour 3" /> The special's script describes Saun Dann's actions while giving Attichitcuk to be "as if he is giving [Attichitcuk] the most X-rated piece of literature in the galaxy."<ref name="Script">''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'' script as posted on the fansite [http://www.starwarsholidayspecial.com/swhs-old/text/script.htm StarWarsHolidaySpecial.com]</ref>

Pornography was first identified by name in an official ''[[Star Wars]]'' source via the ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' sourcebook ''[[Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters]]'', written by [[Mark Rein-Hagen]] and [[Stewart Wieck]] and published by [[West End Games]] in [[1990]].<ref name="GG6" /> Furthermore, the [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] story "[[Smuggler's Blues]]" written by the [[Fillbach Brothers]] identifies it as "smut." The story was included in the [[Star Wars Tales 14|fourteenth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Tales]]'' comic book series by [[Dark Horse Comics]],<ref name="SB" /> released on [[December 11]], [[2002]].<ref name="Marvel">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/53992/star_wars_tales_1999_14|text=Star Wars Tales (1999) 14}}</ref> In the real world, [[Wikipedia:Pornography|pornography]] is the depiction of erotic behavior.<ref name="IRL">{{WebCite|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/pornography|text=Pornography Definition & Meaning|work=Merriam&ndash;Webster|archivedate=20240815041515}}</ref>

